Understood! In that case, you can use the `multer` middleware in combination with the `csv-parser` library to achieve this. Here's an example of how you can upload a CSV file to a REST API endpoint in a Lambda function:

```javascript
const multer = require('multer');
const csv = require('csv-parser');

exports.handler = async (event) => {
    try {
        const file = await processUpload(event);
        const parsedData = await processCSV(file.buffer);

        // Process the parsed CSV data here
        console.log(parsedData);

        return {
            statusCode: 200,
            body: 'CSV file uploaded and processed successfully!',
        };
    } catch (error) {
        console.error(error);
        return {
            statusCode: 500,
            body: 'Error uploading or processing CSV file',
        };
    }
};

const processUpload = (event) => {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        const storage = multer.memoryStorage();
        const upload = multer({ storage }).single('file');

        upload(event, null, (error) => {
            if (error) {
                reject(error);
            } else {
                resolve(event.file);
            }
        });
    });
};

const processCSV = (fileBuffer) => {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        const results = [];

        fileBuffer
            .pipe(csv())
            .on('data', (data) => results.push(data))
            .on('end', () => resolve(results))
            .on('error', (error) => reject(error));
    });
};
```

To use this code, you need to make sure that your API Gateway configuration is set up to pass the file as the `file` field in the encoded form data. The `multer` middleware will handle the file upload and store it in memory. Then, the `csv-parser` library will process the CSV data from the buffer and return it in a structured format for further processing.

Note: This example assumes that you are using API Gateway as the REST API endpoint. Adjust the code accordingly if you are using a different framework or HTTP library.

